## Part 1 — Press Release

(Imagine the finding has been completed. Write the press release as
if announcing it to a skeptical domain audience. 200-400 words,
one page hard limit.)

**[YYYY-MM-DD] — <REPLACE: headline that states the finding in 1
sentence. Include scope and mechanism if possible.>**

<REPLACE: Lead paragraph (1-2 sentences). What was found, in concrete
terms. State the phenomenon, the mechanism, and the scope conditions.>

<REPLACE: Supporting paragraph (1-2 sentences). The discriminating
evidence — what alternative explanations were ruled out, and how. Cite
the type of evidence (numerical / structural / null-result).>

<REPLACE: Implications paragraph (1-2 sentences). What changes
downstream of this finding — practitioners, theory, future research.
Be honest about scope.>

<REPLACE: Closing paragraph (1-2 sentences). What was NOT shown — the
limits of the finding, what next.>

